  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3584",
  "title": "Question: using 'numericMenu' for date range",
  "body": "I have a layout that displays Agenda items based on a start and end date. What I would like to have is a `<select>` element to filter the items on:\r\n\r\n- All\r\n- This week\r\n- This month\r\n\r\nThe widget [numericMenu](https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-reference/widgets/numeric-menu/js/) looks like the right candidate for the job, as it can be used to set specific bounds for each option. In my case that would be the beginning and ending of the current week or month. The problem is that it only accepts an `attribute` as a string for a single value. I have two values, start and end date.\r\n\r\nSo for example:\r\n> An Agenda item starts at **March 4, 2019** and ends at **March 15, 2019**\r\n> When selecting 'This week' the item should only show in **week number 10 & 11**\r\n> When selecting 'This month' the item should only show in **March**\r\n\r\nIs there a way to accomplish this?",
